description: The House passed a bill late Monday that officially makes the bald eagle the national bird. The bill now goes to President Biden for his signature. While most people thought the bald eagle already carried that distinction, it had never received full congressional approval. NBC News' Ryan Nobles reports.
title: House passes bill to make the bald eagle the official U.S. bird
